- Wed 21 Aug 2019. Epidemiological situation report
[CMRE (Comite Multisectoriel de la Riposte a la maladie a virus Ebola), in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
URL unavailable

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 20 Aug 2019:

- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 2927, of which 2822 are confirmed and 105 are probable. In total, there have been 1961 deaths (1856 in confirmed and 105 in probable cases) and 877 people have recovered;
- 382 suspected cases are under investigation;
- 18 new confirmed cases, including 17 in North Kivu, 4 in Butembo, 3 in Katwa, 2 in Beni, 2 in Mutwanga, 2 in Oicha, 1 in Alimbongo, 1 in Kayna, 1 in Mabalako, and 1 in Musienene; and 1 in Ituri, in Mandima;
- 8 new deaths of confirmed cases in North Kivu -- 3 in North Kivu, including 1 in Butembo, 1 in Katwa and 1 in Musienene; 4 deaths in the Ebola treatment center (ETC) in North Kivu, including 3 in the ETC of Butembo and 1 in the ETC of Mabalako; and 1 death in the ETC in North Kivu at Beni;
- 2 people who recovered left the ETC in North Kivu at Beni;
- No new confirmed health workers are among the new confirmed cases. The cumulative confirmed/probable cases among health workers are 154 (5% of all confirmed/probable cases), including 41 deaths.

