- Tue 20 August 2019. WHO: Situation report 55
[World Health Organization Regional Office for Africa, abridged, edited]
https://www.who.int/publications-detail/ebola-virus-disease-democratic-republic-of-congo-external-situation-report-55-2019

Ebola Virus disease Democratic Republic of Congo: external situation report 55 / 2019
Data as reported by 18 Aug 2019
-------------------------------

In the past week, 57 new confirmed Ebola virus disease (EVD) cases with an additional 46 deaths have been reported from 18 health zones in 3 affected provinces in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC). In the 21 days from 29 Jul through 18 Aug 2019, 65 health areas in 18 health zones reported new cases, representing 10% of the 665 health areas in North Kivu, South Kivu and Ituri provinces [see Table 1 and Figure 2 at the source URL]. During this period, a total of 215 confirmed cases were reported, with the majority coming from the health zones of Beni (33%, n = 70) and Mandima (20%, n = 44).

Cases were detected in 2 new health zones this past week: Mwenga Health Zone in South Kivu and Pinga Health Zone in North Kivu. In Mwenga, 3 confirmed cases have been reported thus far after 2 individuals (mother and child) had contact with a confirmed case in Beni before travelling south. The 3rd confirmed case was a co-patient in a community health facility where the 1st cases initially sought care. In Pinga, one confirmed case has been reported, and investigations are ongoing to identify epidemiological links between this individual and outbreak-affected areas. Rapid response teams were quickly deployed to scale up surveillance and response operations in both areas.

As of 18 Aug 2019, a total of 2888 EVD cases were reported, including 2794 confirmed and 94 probable cases, of which 1938 cases died (overall case fatality ratio, 67%). Of the total confirmed and probable cases with reported sex and age, 58% (1672) were female and 28% (810) were children aged less than 18 years. Cases continue to be reported among health workers, with the cumulative number infected rising to 153 (5% of all confirmed and probable cases).

