- Tue 20 Aug 2019. North Kivu (Butembo): violence
[7sur7.cd, in French, machine trans., edited]
https://7sur7.cd/2019/08/20/butembo-des-degats-materiels-enregistres-dans-une-incursion-rebelle-au-centre-de-sante
[Byline: Joel Kaseso]

Armed men, Mai-Mai militants, this Tuesday [20 Aug 2019] attacked the Kambuli Health Center, a health facility located in the Ngingi District, in Mususa commune in the town of Butembo (North Kivu). The information delivered to 7SUR7.CD by Mbaytoya Bovick, bourgmestre [mayor] of the said commune, indicates that the enemy, during his visit, vandalized all material goods of the Kambuli Health Center. "Several material assets have been vandalized, including the malicious destruction of the Ebola Prevention Kits," he said.

The municipal authority of Mususa calls, moreover, the inhabitants of Ngingi for calm while reassuring them of importance of the security forces and defense deployed in the region.

--
communicated by:
Mary Marshall

- Wed 21 Aug 2019. South Kivu (Kavimvira border)
[Radio Okapi, in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://www.radiookapi.net/2019/08/21/actualite/sante/sud-kivu-les-mesures-de-lutte-contre-ebola-renforcees-la-frontiere-de

The number of people leaving the DRC to Burundi by the Kavimvira post has increased from 800 to 1300 per day since last weekend, said the head of the Directorate General of Migration (DGM) in Kavimvira on Tuesday [20 Aug 2019]. Ebola virus disease control systems have been strengthened in this role.

Travelers from the Congolese territory of Mwenga, who had recently encountered difficulties on their way to Rwandan territory, headed for the Congolese-Burundian border from Kavimvira to Gatumba. The migratory flow has increased, confirms the head of the DGM in Kavimvira, evoking long queues observed these days at the exit counters in the morning.

To prevent the occurrence of Ebola, a new handwashing device was installed for vehicle drivers, in addition to the old one that was made available to passengers and other travelers. However, the border health postmaster, Jonas Mafresi Mwanawabene, says control is fraught with difficulties. "We need a thermal camera, devices that are well suited. We have a hand washing water problem from REGIDESO to be able to conduct this activity well. And the vaccine is not yet available in Kavimvira for the personnel of the border health post, the DGM, the police and the army."

--
